text.tspan: Mean income or consumption per day, 2019
This data is adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
Note: This data is measured in international-$ at 2017 prices. Depending on the country and year, it
relates to either disposable income or consumption per capita.
Data source: World Bank PIP; HYDE (2017); Gapminder (2022); UN (2022)
